content:
I've updated the example test case with a full "advanced" FizzBuzz on 1..20, to make immediately apparent that this isn't "normal" FizzBuzz. And to make the I/O direction a bit more obvious.

And I've approved.
The idea is nice and I agree with nicola's comment on a harder version. I have edited the statement to make it clearer and remove the typos.
I wonder if it is possible to create a harder version of this puzzle where the numbers are much larger (ie you have to find a formula or a smarter algorithm).
